  "body": "#### System information\r\n```\r\n$ geth version\r\nGeth\r\nVersion: 1.9.14-unstable\r\nGit Commit: 5c3993444d725aba00c7c8c976c5cc9f4bf6a317\r\nGit Commit Date: 20200427\r\nArchitecture: amd64\r\nProtocol Versions: [65 64 63]\r\nGo Version: go1.13.7\r\nOperating System: darwin\r\nGOPATH=\r\nGOROOT=/usr/local/go\r\n```\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nAfter correctly starting `clef` and `geth --signer /path/to/clef.ipc`, a call to `eth_sign` (or any other signing API) with a valid account should succeed.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nThe call fails with error `unknown account`.   \r\nIf `eth_accounts` or `personal_listWallets` is called before the signing API, the call succeeds.\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1. Start clef\r\n1. Start geth with `--signer /path/to/clef.ipc`\r\n1. Call `eth_sign` with an account known to be available to clef - the sign will fail\r\n1. Call `eth_accounts`\r\n1. Call `eth_sign` with the same account - the sign will now succeed\r\n\r\n#### Cause\r\nThe `ExternalSigner` implementation of `accounts.Wallet` uses `cache []accounts.Account` to look up accounts that are available for signing.  This cache is populated by calls to `eth_accounts` (and a few other methods).\r\n",
